title: 'America's Next Top Model' leaving the runway in December
text:
Updated: 5:23 p.m. Wednesday, Oct. 14, 2015 | Posted: 5:23 p.m. Wednesday, Oct. 14, 2015 'America's Next Top Model' leaving the runway in December Sponsored Links 
TV's "America's Next Top Model" is leaving the runway. 
The CW reality competition series will wrap in December with the current season's finale. 
In a statement Wednesday, network President Mark Pedowitz called the series "a global pop culture phenomenon." 
Tyra Banks, the show's host and executive producer, just launched the syndicated daytime talk show "FABLife." 
"America's Next Top Model" debuted in 2003 on the now-defunct UPN channel and was the first series to debut on fledgling CW in 2006. 
The "America's Next Top Model" finale will air Dec. 4. 
There may be another chance to say goodbye. The network is discussing a retrospective that would air in late 2016. Copyright The Associated Press Sign up for our WPXI-TV Daily Headlines Newsletter Sign Up
